-- Indian shares end higher; blue-chips gain
-- By Indulal PM
-- Mon Oct 13, 2014 06:11AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Oct 13 (Reuters) - Indian shares gained on Monday, as stocks of blue-chip companies recovered from recent losses, tracking positive cues from the European markets, while technology shares rose for a second day.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> provisionally gained 0.33 percent to 26,384.07 points, while the broader NSE index <.NSEI> ended 0.31 percent higher at 7,884.25.